experience.description: Produced an average of 342 baked items per week, maintaining a high quality of freshness and a steady 7.3% annual growth in overall sales. Monitored all baking equipment performance with WebstaurantStore, lowering equipment downtime instances by 21% through proactive maintenance schedules. Managed bakery finances and payroll for a team of 7 using QuickBooks. Used KitchenAid mixers for doughs, batters, and icings, helping new bakers prepare cakes 13 minutes faster.

Assisted the senior baker in producing 78 pastry items daily, ensuring the restaurant received an average of 4.6 rating for its baked food section. Checked baking temperatures on all foods with precision, ensuring all prepared food was of optimal temperature throughout tenure. Helped in decorating custom cake orders using Cake Boss software, encouraging local residents to order custom cakes and increasing overall monthly revenue by 5.8%. Adapted to baking techniques taught by the senior baker to accommodate special dietary requests, such as gluten-free and vegan options.

Contributed to the preparation and packing of organic daily meals, serving an average of 293 supermarket customers daily with exceptional service and quality. Implemented organizing principles learned from Coursera in the storeroom, improving space utilization by 29%. Reduced production expenses by 3% through the negotiation of bulk orders with local vendors. Promoted the idea of having a food labeling system based on the Paprika app's inventory feature, helping the team reduce misplacement and spoilage events by 14%.
